The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  gained 1.3 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
added 0.1 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  climbed 0.5 percent.  New World Resources NV  (NWR CP): The largest Czech producer
of coking coal bid 3.4 billion zloty ($1.19 billion) to buy
 Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA  (LWB PW), Poland’s only publicly
traded coal producer. NWR shares increased 0.2 percent to 210.4
koruna, and Bogdanka declined 0.2 percent to 89.05 zloty.  PGE SA  (PGE PW): Polish Prime Minister  Donald Tusk  will
meet this month with  Malgorzata Krasnodebska-Tomkiel , head of
the country’s antitrust watchdog, to discuss the government’s
planned sale of power utility Energa SA to PGE, a deal the
regulator opposes. PGE declined 1.4 percent to 22.93 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Pawel Kozlowski  in Warsaw 
 pkozlowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
